 ## Entries
 
 - **tao-averaged-ns-delayed-transfer-circuit.md** — Tao's averaged-NS blowup mechanism is a deliberately engineered five-mode delayed-abrupt-transfer circuit embedded in a shell cascade, not a vague "dyadic cascade" slogan. Averaging preserves energy cancellation/scaling but not the exact local NS tensor structure. Key reduced roles: `X1,n` carrier, `X2,n` clock, `X3,n` tiny trigger, `X4,n` conduit, `X1,n+1` next carrier. The sharpened exact-NS firewall question is whether real triads can realize the same independently tuned couplings/signs while suppressing parasitic interactions. [VERIFIED]
 - **exact-helical-near-closed-tao-circuit-definition.md** — Phase 0 definition gate PASSES: a near-closed Tao circuit can be stated exactly on a finite sign-closed helical support with a five-role target hypergraph and a coefficient-weighted leakage ratio. Exact data and user tolerances are now explicitly separated. Singleton amplitude-level bookkeeping is the preferred Phase 1 object; packet-energy models are backup only. [CHECKED]
